Use what you have learned to decide what you think would best help the farm.
Here are some facts to help:
Lucy has trees on her farm that she can use to build hives.
Lucy will have to remove some corn crops to add cotton crops.
Lucy has $127 that she can spend. To add a fence she needs 210 meters of wire. The wire costs $1 per meter.

attributes.value: Add beehives around the corn crops. The elephants will see the beehives and be scared away.

components.content: Add beehives around the corn crops. The elephants will see the beehives and be scared away.

attributes.value: Plant cotton crops around the corn crops to attract bees. The bees will scare away the elephants.

components.content: Plant cotton crops around the corn crops to attract bees. The bees will scare away the elephants.

attributes.value: Build a barbed wire fence. The barbs will hurt the elephants and stop them from entering the farm.

components.content:
Build a barbed wire fence.
                The barbs will hurt the elephants and stop them from entering the farm.
